Subject: [PATCH] Add global data-collection deny valve

This patch adds a valve that forces `provider.data_collection="deny"` on every
OpenRouter request to restrict providers that store user data.

Highlights:
- Adds ENFORCE_DATA_COLLECTION_DENY valve (default: True)
- Injects provider.data_collection="deny" for all requests

To apply: git apply patches/0008-add-data-collection-deny-valve.patch
To revert: git apply -R patches/0008-add-data-collection-deny-valve.patch

Note: This patch modifies existing upstream files. When upstream updates these
files, you may need to resolve merge conflicts.
